###How to fix the Common Vulnerabilities issue of CVE-2019-0217
CVE-2019-0217 is a race condition vulnerability in Apache HTTP Server 2.4 release 2.4.38 and prior. This vulnerability could allow an attacker with valid credentials to authenticate using another username, bypassing configured access control restrictions.

To fix this vulnerability, you should upgrade your Apache HTTP Server to a version that is at least 2.4.39. If you are unable to upgrade, you can apply the following patch:

```
https://httpd.apache.org/security/vulnerabilities_24.html#CVE-2019-0217
```

This vulnerability belongs to the OWASP Top 10 Web Application Security Risks 2021 category of "Broken Authentication and Session Management".

Here are some additional steps you can take to improve the security of your Apache HTTP Server:

* Use strong passwords and enable password hashing.
* Enable HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) to force all connections to be made over HTTPS.
* Enable HTTP Public Key Pinning to prevent attackers from serving malicious content over HTTPS.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to block common attack vectors.
* Monitor your Apache HTTP Server for signs of attack.
